Responsible Social Media Use Checklist for College Students

Do’s
Think before you post – Make sure your content is respectful and appropriate.
Protect your privacy – Use strong passwords and adjust privacy settings.
Verify information before sharing – Avoid spreading misinformation or fake news.
Be respectful and kind – Engage in positive and constructive conversations.
Manage your time wisely – Set limits to avoid excessive social media use.

Don’ts
Don’t share personal or sensitive information –  phone number, address, etc.
Don’t engage in cyberbullying or trolling – It can harm others and your reputation.
Don’t believe everything you see online – Always cross-check sources.
Don’t overshare your daily life – Maintain a healthy boundary.
Don’t post in anger or frustration – Emotional posts can have long-term consequences.
